 Terry, Gerrard to be consulted
THE DAILY TELEGRAPHLondon: John Terry and Steven Gerrard are to be consulted by Brian Barwick over who the next England manager should be. The Football Association chief executive on Friday began his search for Steve McClarens successor and wants the advice of senior players such as Terry, the team captain, and Gerrard, the vice-captain. Barwicks move deserves praise, although it needs stressing that the players are not picking the next England manager. They are merely being invited to offer their thoughts to assist Barwick in his hunt for the man to lead Terry, Gerrard and the rest of Englands underachievers out of the international wilderness. 
